umbing/recovery, not translation quality.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.76,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The dictionary-based fallback returns the correct pre-stored translation for phrases that exist in the SQLite database.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is fallback module + real SQLite data access. A pure unit test of lookup logic misses SQL/schema/query mapping issues (MOCK-MISS=yes). No real network/subprocess needed (REAL-INFRA=no), no model-quality dependency (LLM-DEP=no).","test_description":"Use a test SQLite DB with seeded phrase pairs, execute fallback translator lookup for existing phrases, and assert returned text matches stored translation.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The quality tracking comparison correctly computes edit distance between primary and fallback outputs and stores the metric.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Although edit-distance math can be unit-tested, this behavior also requires persistence of the computed metric, making module wiring/storage part of the failure boundary. Real AI output is not required; deterministic strings reproduce failures in compute+store path (LLM-DEP demoted). No OS/network/subprocess requirement (REAL-INFRA=no).","test_description":"Provide fixed primary/fallback strings, run quality-tracking path, assert stored metric equals expected character-level edit distance in persistence layer.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"IA-UA demotion proof: behavior text is \"computes edit distance ... and stores the metric\"; it does not assert whether model output is semantically correct.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.32,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When both translators